<HEADLINE> Equity Prices in Greece Surge to Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Equity prices in Greece hit an
all-time high Tuesday with the general index on the Athens Stock
Exchange (ASE) ending 1.48 percent up at 5,705.10 points.
</P>
<P>
This is the 47th record for the ASE general index since the
beginning of this year. The ASE general index jumped 3.95 percent
to 5,621.67 points Monday.
</P>
<P>
The general index has recorded gains of 108.4 percent since the
first session of this year.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was more than 400 billion drachmas (about 1.32 billion
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Advancers led decliners by 203 to 105 with four issues
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The holding and construction sectors led the increasing stock
market with rising 6.71 percent and 3.95 percent respectively.
</P>
</TEXT>
