<HEADLINE> Police Arrest BBC Television Centre Intruder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Police on Tuesday arrested a
man who burst into the BBC's television headquarters in London.
</P>
<P>
The motive for the outburst was unclear.
</P>
<P>
"He was arrested on suspicion of burglary and taken into
custody but has not yet been charged," a Scotland Yard spokeswoman
told Reuters.
</P>
<P>
"He was a 20-year old, unemployed, believed to be from Surrey.
He was not armed and nobody was injured," she said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Tuesday the unnamed man broke through security by
jumping over the main entry barriers and got to the first floor
where he smashed a glass wall with a table to gain entry to the
news centre.
</P>
<P>
He started throwing around monitors and printers until he was
overpowered by BBC staff.
</P>
<P>
"We are not aware of any reason as to why this attack might
have happened," the BBC spokeswoman said.
</P>
<P>
The BBC was tightening its security at the public building
after the incident.
</P>
<P>
It also launched a security investigation to find out how the
man reached the heart of the BBC's news operation despite extra
security imposed since one of its top personalities Jill Dando was
murdered outside her home earlier this year in a hit-man style
shooting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
