<HEADLINE> Argentina Denies Handing Over Base to U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENAS AIRES, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Argentine Interior
Minister Carlos Corach on Tuesday denied that Argentina has a
training base for U.S. military personnel.
</P>
<P>
The Argentine cooperation with the U.S. military is limited to
joint exercises, confirmed Corach at a press conference.
</P>
<P>
"Argentina is handing over no bases, land or any type of
deposits", to the U.S. army in the province of Misiones, on the
border with Brazil, he added.
</P>
<P>
The interior minister confirmed that works carried out in the
jungle territory of Misiones is limited to joint exercises of
combat in which the U.S. and other countries have participated.
</P>
<P>
"Brazil can and has participated in military exercises with
Argentina", he said.
</P>
<P>
According to a Buen Aires newspaper, "Clarin", the fact that
the U.S. military are participating in the exercises at the
military camp of "Montez" in Misiones has angered Brazil. 
</P>
</TEXT>
