<HEADLINE> OPEC President to Visit UAE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Algerian Energy Minister
and President of the Organization of Oil Exporting Countries
(OPEC) Youcef Yousfi will visit the United Arab Emirates (UAE)
next week.
</P>
<P>
The visit is part of a Gulf tour the OPEC leader intends to
carry out prior to the organization's ministerial meeting in
Vienna later this month, the official WAM news agency reported
on Tuesday
</P>
<P>
During his tour, Yousfi will discuss with Gulf oil leaders
the situation in the world oil market, as well as topics in
the agenda of the Vienna meeting.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a UAE oil ministry source told WAM that oil
ministers of the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC), which comprises
the UAE, Saudi Arabia, Oman, Kuwait, Qatar and Bahrain, would
meet in Riyadh on September 18.
</P>
<P>
The ministers are expected to coordinate their stands on
the oil market ahead of the OPEC meeting.
</P>
<P>
Analysts predict that the OPEC ministerial meeting would
probably keep the oil output curb accord reached by major oil
producers intact until April 2000.
</P>
<P>
OPEC members and non-OPEC producers Mexico, Norway, Oman and
Russia agreed to cut output by 2.1 million barrels per day
last March.
</P>
<P>
Oil prices have risen dramaticly since this move was carried
out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
