<HEADLINE> Tripoli Witnesses Grand Military Parade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TRIPOLI, September 7 (Xinhua) -- A grand military parade
was held here Tuesday highlighting the ongoing celebrations for
the country's 30th anniversary of the Libyan Revolution.
</P>
<P>
Libyan leader Muammar Ghaddafi, Secretary General of the Arab
League Ahamed Meguid, Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat, Heads of
State and Government of the member states of the Organization of
African Unity (OAU) witnessed the event which was staged on the
Al Fateh Street in the capital Tripoli.
</P>
<P>
Symbolic military units from 32 OAU member states joined
brigades of the Libyan armed forces and marched to the tune of
martial music in a show of African unity and determination to
safeguard the security of the continent.
</P>
<P>
The air forces put on an air show with formations of Mig-23
and Mirage-F1 fighter jets, helicopters, bombers, personnel
carriers and transporters.
</P>
<P>
Woman soldiers from the Libyan Military Academy and Eritrea
also participated in the four-hour parade.
</P>
<P>
African leaders and dignitaries were also saluted by Libya's
10 tank battalions, mechanized infantry battalions, artillery
battalions, air-defense artillery battalions and
surface-to-surface missile brigades.
</P>
<P>
On September 1, 1969, a group of officers under col. Muammar
Ghaddafi overthrew the Monarchy in a military coup and proclaimed
the Libyan Arab Republic. In October, 1986, the country was
renamed the Great Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahirya.
</P>
</TEXT>
