<HEADLINE> Cypriot Bank Gains Record Profits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Cypriot Popular Bank
gained record operating profits in the first six months of 1999,
the Popular Bank Group's Executive Chairman Kikis Lazarides said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Profits of the bank reached 36.7 million Cyprus pounds (72.4
million U.S. dollars) compared with 24 million pounds (48 million
dollars) the same period last year, registering a 42.5 percent
increase.
</P>
<P>
Shareholders will be given an interim dividend of 10 percent,
compared with 8 percent last year.
</P>
<P>
Lazarides said the impressive results are partly due to the
Group's expansion in the insurance sector, the spectacular
increase in the stock exchange activity and the effective control
of operating costs.
</P>
<P>
"Prospects for the next half of the year appear even more
positive," he said, noting that the Group had very good results in
the insurance and stock exchange sectors.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the local economy, Lazarides warned a rising
public deficit would pose serious danger for the stability of the
economy at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
He described the Group as "a robust modern organization,
capable to meet future challenges and serve its customers."
</P>
</TEXT>
