<HEADLINE> Viacom to Buy CBS in Largest U.S. Media Merger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Viacom, the owner of
Paramount film studio and cable music network MTV announced here
Tuesday that it is buying television network CBS for 35 billion
U.S. dollars in the biggest U.S. media merger so far.
</P>
<P>
The acquisition would create a large multi-media company, just
second to Time Warner, parent of CNN and would rank a leading
producer of entertainment, news, sports and music.
</P>
<P>
The new company, keeping Viacom as its name, will combine the
broadcasting might of CBS with the cable and movie-producing
assets of Viacom.
</P>
<P>
U.S. media business has not seen such a big merger since Walt
Disney bought Capital Cities/ABC for 19 billion dollars in 1996.
</P>
</TEXT>
