<HEADLINE> Yemen Uncovers Causes of Recent Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- With intensive and unremitting
investigations, the Yemeni security agencies have uncovered the
causes of the explosion that took place in downtown Sanaa on
August 28 morning.
</P>
<P>
The explosion in Sanna's "City Center" shop was caused by some
sort of highly-inflammable materials (oil or gas) and no explosive
substances were used in it, the Yemeni News Agency Tuesday quoted
a security official as saying.
</P>
<P>
The explosion was planned by the owner and some workers of City
Centre due to financial difficulties undergone by the centre. The
culprits sought, through the explosion, to get compensations from
the insurance company, the official said.
</P>
<P>
The security agencies got these categorical facts from the
confessions of some suspects who were proven to be accomplices in
the criminal act, he said. The conclusions were in line with the
results of the criminal lab, he added.
</P>
<P>
The explosion left two persons dead, namely, Abdullah Al-Emeiri
- the owner of the centre - and Khaled Hussein Musaad who lived in
a neighboring house. Twelve others were slightly injured.
</P>
<P>
The case will be referred to the judiciary, the security
official said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that some alien elements tried to mar Yemen's
image as usual but to no avail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
