<HEADLINE> Wust Wins Third Stage at Tour of Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Marcel Wust of Germany won the
third stage at the Tour of Spain on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Wust, who won the second stage on Monday, also took over the
leader's golden jersey after winning the 229.5-kilometer third
stage from La Roda to Fuenlabrada.
</P>
<P>
It was Wust's tenth stage win in Tour of Spain races. He now
leads Robbie MeEwen of Australia by 9 seconds in the overall
standings.
</P>
<P>
Giovanni Lombardi of Italy finished second in the stage,
followed by Sergei Smetanini of Russia in the third place.
</P>
<P>
Spanish rider German Nieto led alone for 190 kilometers and
once built up a 20 minutes lead. But he was so tired in the last
8 kilometers and finished several minutes behind the leaders.
</P>
<P>
The 185.6-kilometer fourth stage will be held on Wednesday.
</P>
