<HEADLINE> China, Britain - Partners For Future: DTI </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 7 (Xinhua) -- China has a major role to play
in ensuring "the long term strength and stability of the world
economy" which is why the UK supports the principle of China's
accession to the World Trade Organization, a British senior
official said.
</P>
<P>
A press release by the Department of Trade and Industry quoted
Trade Minister Richard Caborn as saying Tuesday: "We want to see
China in the WTO for China's benefit, for our benefit and for the
benefit of World Trade."
</P>
<P>
"Membership would ensure that China's trade partners enjoy
improved market access and a stable environment for investment and
trade," he added.
</P>
<P>
Caborn, who has been invited to speak on an international
investment seminar in China Wednesday, said he "will use the
opportunity to underline the strong confidence the UK Government
has in China's future as a key global trade and investment
partner".
</P>
<P>
Britain is now the 6th largest global investor in China and by
far the leading European investor with British companies involved
in more than 2000 joint ventures.
</P>
<P>
Pledged investment in China by British companies was more than
13 billion U.S. dollars in 1998. In 1999, they have increased by
30 percent to date, compared with last year. 
</P>
