<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Declares State of Emergency in Amazon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANIERO, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's Environment
Ministry Tuesday declared a state of alert in the Amazon and
prohibited the act of land clearing by the use of fire, in a
measure taken to prevent forest fires.
</P>
<P>
The authorities are afraid that because of the drought and the
absence of rain in the Amazon, any fire may grow to enormous
proportions, as happened last year in the province of Roraima.
</P>
<P>
Fire-fighters have combated around 2,000 forest fires in 15 of
the 27 states.
</P>
<P>
The state of emergency ordered by the civil authorities and
military forces, as well as those in charge of the environment,
assures that the aforementioned services are ready to act in the
case of any forest fire in the Amazon region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
