<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Some 600 people were
evacuated Tuesday from their suburban Detroit homes in Michigan
State, the United States, as a precaution following the derailment
of a railroad tanker that possibly contained a toxic chemical,
reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The tanker may contain ethylene oxide, which can cause severe
burns and "might even have the potential to be lethal if inhaled,"
the reports quoted Ecorse Police Chief Robert Royals as saying.
</P>
