<HEADLINE> London Stock Market Leads Way Down in Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 7 (Xinhua) - London market led the way down
Tuesday in Europe ahead of the Bank of England's decision on
interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE 100 fell just more than 1 percent to 6309.5, a drop of
66 points. Investors opted to pocket gains after the index
advanced 180 points in the last two sessions.
</P>
<P>
"It has been a bit of a weary day, with the market waiting for
tomorrow's policy meeting," said one trader at a UK brokerage.
</P>
<P>
"Nobody expects the Monetary Policy Committee to increase rates
so I'm a bit surprised the market is down across the board," he
added.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the losses for blue chips, the FTSE 250 index
fell 19.8 to 6153.4 and the FTSE 350 index lost 28.5 to close at
3051.9.
</P>
<P>
Telecom stocks led the way down after recent strong gains.
Heavyweights BT.A and VOD gave up just more than 3 percent and 2
percent, respectively. CW. also shed 2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Xetra Dax share index dipped below par in late
Tuesday afternoon trade, closing at 5391 - down 9 points.
</P>
<P>
Investors were reluctant to take fresh positions amid a lull in
corporate news and as US shares came off a strong pre-holiday
rally.
</P>
<P>
French share prices rose to a record high point during trading
on Tuesday when the CAC 40 index reached 4728.61 points, showing a
gain of 1.3 percent from the closing value on Monday.
</P>
<P>
However, at the end of the day the CAC could not hold its gains
and closed at 4679 - unchanged from Monday's close. 
</P>
</TEXT>
