<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1545 GMT September 8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS -- The death toll from Tuesday afternoon's powerful
earthquake in the Greek capital of Athens has risen to 38,
including 14 children and infants.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake measuring 5.9 on the Richter scale occurred at 2:
56 p.m. local time Tuesday and was centered in the Mount Parnitha
region, some 20 kilometers north of Athens.(Greek-Death-Quake)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CANBERRA -- China stands "very firm" on the principle of
safeguarding sovereignty and territorial integrity, visiting
Chinese President Jiang Zemin said here Wednesday during talks
with Australian Prime Minister John Howard.
</P>
<P>
He said that Lee Teng-hui's recent "two states" remarks
represent a very dangerous step towards splitting China, as their
essence is to completely defy and abandon the internationally
acclaimed "one China" stance. (Jiang-Howard-Taiwan)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CANBERRA -- China will by no means abandon the use of force if
there occurs "Taiwan independence" or foreign intervention,
visiting Chinese President Jiang Zemin said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Taiwan issue is purely China's internal affairs and China's
policy on this issue is "peaceful reunification" and the principle
of "one country, two systems", stressed Jiang in a joint press
conference with Australian Prime Minister John Howard following
their official talks in the morning. (Jiang-Taiwan)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CANBERRA -- Visiting Chinese President Jiang Zemin Wednesday
expounded China's principled stand on China' s access to the World
Trade Organization (WTO).
</P>
<P>
At a joint press conference with Australian Prime Minister John
Howard after their meeting, Jiang said he talked with U.S.
President Bill Clinton on the question of restoring the lawful
seat of China in GATT, now called the WTO, during his meeting with
Clinton at the first informal meeting of leaders of Asia-Pacific
Economic Cooperation (APEC) in Seattle of the United States, in
1993. (Jiang-Australia-WTO)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CANBERRA -- Visiting Chinese President Jiang Zemin stressed
here Wednesday the need for China and Australia to undertake
efforts to build a Sino-Australian relationship oriented towards
the new century.(Jiang-Australia-Ties)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CANBERRA -- Visiting Chinese President Jiang Zemin said here
Wednesday that China will continue to develop friendly cooperation
with other countries in the world on the basis of the Five
Principles of Peaceful Coexistence.
</P>
<P>
In a speech at a luncheon hosted by Australian Prime Minister
John Howard, Jiang said the international situation is undergoing
important and profound changes, and peace and development remain
the two major tasks confronting people in the world.(Jiang-World
Situation)  
</P>
