<HEADLINE> China Pledged to Protect Legitimate Rights of Taiwan Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- China will do its utmost to
protect all legitimate rights and interests of Taiwan investors,
no matter what happens to the cross-Straits relations, a senior
Chinese official said here today.
</P>
<P>
"We'll make unremitting efforts to accelerate economic
exchanges and cooperation across the Taiwan Straits," said Li
Bingcai, deputy director of the Taiwan Affairs Office of the State
Council, at the ongoing Third China Investment and Trade Fair.
</P>
<P>
Any attempts to interfere in the cross-Straits economic
development under the pretext of political differences violate
economic law, are unwise, and will be to no avail, Li stressed,
referring to Taiwan leader Lee Teng-hui's separatist "two states"
remark.
</P>
<P>
Li said that Lee's remark has created tension between the two
sides of the Straits and jeopardized both Taiwan's economy and
cross-Straits economic and trade ties.
</P>
<P>
He said that the mainland has been the main target of
investment for Taiwan investors since it has maintained political
and social stability, and rapid and steady economic growth.
</P>
<P>
China will continue to encourage Taiwanese investment in the
mainland and provide more support and better services to Taiwan
investors, Li said.
</P>
<P>
"We'll stick to the principle that economic exchanges across
the Straits should not be affected by any differences," Li added.
</P>
</TEXT>
