<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CV Registrations in UK Down in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The UK's commercial vehicle
registrations in August, traditionally the lead month, declined
this year as customers wait for the September V plate.
</P>
<P>
The overall market is down 69.6 percent, to 13,534 from last
August's 44,549. The LCV was the most heavily affected sector with
registrations, in particular the light 4x4 utilities sector,
according to the figures released by the Society of Manufacturers
and Traders (SMMT).
</P>
<P>
LCVs under 1800kg down by 72.4 percent to 3,386 from 12,272
last August. LCVs between 1801 and 3500kg also dropped 73.1
percent to 6,230 from 23,179, the SMMT said.
</P>
<P>
The light 4x4 utilities plummeted by 85.2 percent, to 335 from
2,261 in 1998. The trucks and artics sector fell by 48.9 percent,
to 3,314 from 6,488.
</P>
<P>
Year to date figures show that the overall commercial vehicle
market is down 10.8 percent, to 181,346 from 203,247 last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
