<HEADLINE> Russia Steps up Strikes on Rebels in Daghestan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Russian federal troops have
started active advancement in western and southern directions of
the village of Karamakhi in Daghestan's Buinaksk district, the
Interior Ministry press service said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
However, elite OMON police and rapid reaction units
encountered setbacks due to mine-fields laid by the rebels in and
around Karamakhi, the Itar-Tass news agency quoted the press
service as saying.
</P>
<P>
Russian air force planes pounded rebel positions near the
village of Chabanmakhi, another stronghold nesting higher in the
foothills of Chaban mountain.
</P>
<P>
So far, Russian forces are engaged in fighting against rebels
in seven villages near the breakaway republic of Chechnya,
striking the Islamic extremists with air, artillery fire and tanks.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, small groups of guerrillas are also trying to
infiltrate into other parts near the village in order to
destabilize the region, Tass said.
</P>
<P>
Four rebel snipers, two mortars, one ZU-23 air-defense system,
five ammunition storage facilities, and three fuel and lubricant
storage facilities were destroyed by the federal forces in the
villages of Karamakhi and Chabanmakhi Tuesday, the Interfax news
agency quoted the Interior Ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
The rebels damaged two Interior Ministry helicopters, and put
one tank, six armored vehicles and one anti-aircraft system out of
commission, Interfax said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
