<HEADLINE> China Continues Opening-up: Wu Yi (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To attract more overseas investment for China's sustained,
speedy and sound development, the Chinese government recently has
taken a series of measures to create an even better environment
for overseas investors and offer better conditions for foreign
trade, Wu said.
</P>
<P>
She suggested that overseas investors seek business
opportunities in such areas as technical renovation of state-owned
enterprises, development of China's vast central and western
regions, high- and new-technology projects, infrastructure, and
the service trade.
</P>
<P>
Wu believed that China will definitely will play a more
important role in international investment cooperation in the 21st
century, thanks to its ongoing progress in reform and opening-up,
the gradual establishment of the socialist market economy, and its
steadily improved investment environment.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this morning, Wu attended the opening ceremony of the
Third China Fair for International Investment and Trade.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday she met with Donald Johnston, secretary-general of
the Organization of Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD),
and Toshio Miyoshi, chairman of the Japan-China Economic Relations
and Trade Center. 
