<HEADLINE> Scenic Lake Named a World Heritage Candidate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The West Lake, a scenic lake
in east China, has been named by the Chinese government as one of
over 20 local applicants for the World Heritage list.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made by an official from the Ministry of
Construction at a local seminar on the culture of the West Lake,
which was held in Hangzhou, the capital of Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The lake is known for its abundance of lotus flowers in the
summer, and beautiful surroundings with classical gardens and
green hills. 
