<HEADLINE> China Starts Mass Production of Color LCD Screens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- China began its mass production
of color LCD screens today with the opening of a large factory in
Dalian, a coastal city in northwest China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The manufacturer, The Dalian Dongfu Color LCD Screen Factory,
is jointly funded by two local companies a Taiwan-based firm.
</P>
<P>
The factory, which uses equipment from Taiwan and Japan, cost
29 million U.S. dollars and can produce 160,000 square meters of
world-class color LCD screens a year.
</P>
<P>
All of its products will be exported and are expected to earn
97.2 million U.S. dollars annually.
</P>
<P>
China has become one of the largest producers of color LCD
screens in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
