<HEADLINE> Giant Musical Fountain Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A giant musical fountain began
spouting and playing tunes today at Orient Square along Chang'an
Avenue in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
The computerized fountain, with 980 spouts, can form dozens of
varieties of fountain art, accompanied by a diverse range of
background melodies.
</P>
<P>
It has 478 lights under water, which produce a colorful laser
effect and can form a 30x5 meter water screen on which to show
movies.
</P>
<P>
Funding for the 33-meter-long elliptical fountain was donated
by Li Ka-shing, a Hong Kong-based entrepreneur. 
