<HEADLINE> Iran, Japan 1-1 in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Ali Daei scored an equalizer to
give Asian Games champions Iran a 1-1 draw with Japan in a soccer
friendly at Yokohama, Japan, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian team was given a free kick after Japanese goal-
keeper Yoshikatsu Kawaguchi touched the ball out of the penalty
area.
</P>
<P>
Ali Daei, who now plays for Gundesliga club Hertha Berlin,
struck into the left side from just out of the area at the 68th
minute.
</P>
<P>
Japan scored a lucky goal 10 minutes into the match when
DAisuke Oku's shot from outside the penalty hit a defender's leg
and went into the goal.
</P>
<P>
Japan's head coach Philippe Troussier admitted the 1-1 draw was
a good result for the Japanese as the Iranian team had many
chances to score.
</P>
<P>
"It was a difficult match. The Iranian team have physical
strength and experience and a very good forward like Daei." said
Troussier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
