<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Market Driving Force Behind HK Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The vast Chinese market will
continue to be the driving force behind Hong Kong's economic
growth, the financial secretary of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region said here today.
</P>
<P>
"A sustained and highly prosperous economy in the interior
areas is in the best interest of the Hong Kong people," Donald
Tsang said at the Symposium on International Investment and
Cooperation for the 21st Century, which opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Tsang said that from a long-term perspective, Hong Kong should
conform its economy with that of the interior areas, especially
the neighboring Pearl Zhujiang River Delta and Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
By doing so, Tsang said, Hong Kong will be more qualified for
regional and global competition.
</P>
<P>
Tsang said that the inland is now offering lots of business
opportunities for the Hong Kong people as it is preparing to enter
the World Trade Organization and to open wider its service
industry.
</P>
<P>
Tsang added that the service industry in the inland will catch
up with that of advanced countries in the world in about a dozen
years as the business environment improves.
</P>
<P>
According to Tsang, the Hong Kong people have invested 142.7
billion U.S. dollars in the inland over the past two decades,
accounting for 51 percent of the inland's total investment from
overseas, and this has helped Hong Kong's economic transformation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
