<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SOS Children's Village to Be Built in Xinjiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The foundation stone was laid
today for an internationally-funded children's home to be built in
Urumqi, the capital of the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, in
northwest China.
</P>
<P>
The SOS Children's Village, the eighth in China, is located in
the western suburbs of the city and covers over 33,000 square
meters. It is designed to hold 112 kids who will be grouped into
14 families, each attended by a paid nanny.
</P>
<P>
China has worked with the International SOS Children's Village
Organization since 1984. In 1987, the first two such homes in
China were set up in Tianjin Municipality, in the north, and
Yantai City, in eastern Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The other five SOS Children's Villages are in Qiqihar, Nanchang,
Chengdu, Kaifeng and Putian cities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
