<DOCNO> XIE19990908.0103 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Silver, Gold Prices Up in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Both silver and gold prices
continued to rise Wednesday on the bullion market in Mumbai
(Bombay) due to increased local demand coupled with higher
overseas advises.
</P>
<P>
Ready silver (.999 fineness), after a firm start at 8,075
rupees (187.79 U.S. dollars) per kilogram, eased moderately to
close at 8,070 rupees (187.67 dollars), showing a rise of 20
rupees (0.46 dollars) over the last close of 8,050 rupees (187.21
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Raw silver (.916 fineness) improved by a similar margin to end
at 7,930 rupees (184.42 dollars) per kilogram from the last close
of 7,910 rupees (183.95 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, standard gold rose further by 10 rupees (0.23
dollars) per 10 gram to 4,070 rupees (94.65 dollars) from the last
close of 4,060 rupees (94.42 dollars). 
</P>
