<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin on Regional, World Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese President
Jiang Zemin said here Wednesday that China will continue to
develop friendly cooperation with other countries in the world on
the basis of the Five Principles of Peaceful Coexistence.
</P>
<P>
In a speech at a luncheon hosted by Australian Prime Minister
John Howard, Jiang said the international situation is undergoing
important and profound changes, and peace and development remain
the two major tasks confronting people in the world.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that in the Asia-Pacific region where China and
Australia are located, local destabilizing factors persist and the
negative impact of the financial crisis has yet to be fully
eliminated.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, peace, cooperation and development are the
shared aspiration of people of all countries in the world.
</P>
<P>
"We have always maintained that countries should treat each
other as equals and respect the diversity of the world. National
affairs of a country should be decided by its own people and
international affairs should be solved by all through consultation,
" Jiang said. 
</P>
