<HEADLINE> Sensex Gains in Bombay Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Sensitive Index (SENSEX)
rose 7.97 points Wednesday on the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) due
to bull liquidation despite sustained purchases by Foreign
Institutional Investors.
</P>
<P>
Initially, the BSE-30 share sensitive index showed signs of a
sharp recovery rising to the day's high of 4,827.43. However, it
fell back later sharply to a low of 4,775.13 before closing at
4,781.62 as against Tuesday's close of 4,773.65, netting a minor
gain of 7.97 points.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-100 index gained 13.09 points at 2,146.49 over the
previous close of 2,136.40.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 index and the Dollex were quoted remarkably up at
497.17 and 190.24 compared with their previous close of 492.66 and
188.60 respectively.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-500 index improved by 13.91 points to 1,472.20 from
Tuesday's close of 1,458.29. 
</P>
</TEXT>
