<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets Nepalese Former PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua)-- Li Peng, chairman of the
Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress NPC),
met with Sher Bahadur Deupa, former prime minister of Nepal, at
the Great Hall of the People today.
</P>
<P>
Li welcomed Deupa on behalf of the NPC Standing Committee and
said he believes Deupa's current visit will help advance bilateral
ties.
</P>
<P>
He recalled his visit to Nepal ten years ago, and thanked the
host for the warm hospitality he received then. Tracing the
history of friendship between the two countries, Li said that even
the Himalayas standing between the two countries cannot separate
such an enduring friendship.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed thanks for the Nepalese Government's support
to China on world issues, and for its firm stand on the issues of
Tibet and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Deupa thanked the Chinese Government and people for China's
assistance to Nepal in its economic development and efforts to
maintain sovereignty, and congratulated China on the 50th
anniversary of its founding on October 1 and the upcoming return
of Macao.
</P>
<P>
He reaffirmed Nepal's unwavering position on the Tibet and
Taiwan issues, stressing that Nepal will never allow any foreign
forces to use its territory to engage in any activities against
China. 
</P>
