<HEADLINE> Beijing Opera Highlights Historical Figure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Fan Zhongyan, a famous Chinese
historical figure in the Song Dynasty (960-1279), will be brought
to life on the Beijing Opera stage next Monday.
</P>
<P>
The historical opera, presented by the Guiyang Beijing Opera
Troupe in southwest China's Guizhou Province, is part of an arts
program to celebrate the 50th anniversary of the People's Republic
of China.
</P>
<P>
Fan Zhongyan was a famous strategist, statesman, and literary
figure. His literary works have been studied by generations of
scholars, and were selected in textbooks of different periods.
</P>
<P>
This opera, based on Fan's life, highlights the compassion felt
by ancient Chinese intellectuals for ordinary people.
</P>
<P>
According to one reviewer, the Beijing Opera "Fan Zhongyan" is
a vivid representation of a historical figure.
</P>
<P>
Since its debut in Guizhou in 1993, Beijing Opera "Fan Zhongyan
" has been performed more than 100 times.  
</P>
</TEXT>
