<HEADLINE> China Issues Souvenirs for Int'l Year of Old Persons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- China will issue 1,999 jade
souvenirs to commemorate the International Year of Old Persons --
1999.
</P>
<P>
The Gerontological Society of China today presented the gifts
to the Chinese Museum of Revolution and the United Nations'
Program on Aging, in order to focus attention on the problems of
the elderly.
</P>
<P>
The jade pieces are made of Burmese natural jade, designed with
elaborate carvings of the tortoise and snake, traditional Chinese
symbols of health and longevity.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the UN show that by 2001, the worldwide
population of people over 60 will hit 630 million, and is expected
to reach one billion in 2020.
</P>
<P>
China's aging population will exceed 130 million next year; by
the mid-21st century, China will have about 400 million elderly,
the biggest population of old people in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
