<DOCNO> XIE19990908.0127 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Build ID Number Management System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua)-- Every Chinese citizen is
expected to receive a permanent identification number before the
end of next year, an officer with the Ministry of Public Security
said today.
</P>
<P>
He said that the State Council, China's highest governing body,
plans to establish a national identification card (ID) number
management system, starting October 1.
</P>
<P>
The new ID number is significant because it will be used as
proof of identity in daily political, economic and social life and
is closely linked with the rights and interests of all Chinese, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Each ID number consists of eighteen figures, six representing
the owner's administrative area code, eight for the owner's
birthday, three for the individual's serial number, and the last
one for verification. The even serial number stands for male and
the odd for female.
</P>
<P>
The system is to be completed in two years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
