<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Monetary
Authority (HKMA) and Korea Securities Depository (KSD) announced
Wednesday a setup of a bilateral linkage for cross-border debt
securities trading.
</P>
<P>
Citibank was appointed as the Hong Kong Dollar Cash Settlement
Bank for KSD in the bilateral securities linkage between Hong Kong
and South Korea, according to a spokesman for Citibank Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Under the mandate, Citibank Hong Kong will handle the payment
of Hong Kong dollar debt securities, including payment and receipt
of funds and funds transfer for KSD.
</P>
<P>
"This appointment demonstrates our strategic role in helping
promote the Hong Kong dollar debt securities market to
institutional investors in Asia," said T. C. Chan, country
corporate officer for Citibank Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"It is also a recognition of our people, electronic delivery
technology and overall cash management expertise in Asia," Chan
said.
</P>
<P>
Citibank is the first and only bank to provide cash settlement
services to Hong Kong's bilateral linkages with securities
depositories in Asia. 
</P>
