<HEADLINE> Share Prices Drift Down on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Share prices drifted down on
Singapore Stock Market Wednesday continuing the trend toward a
weak performance on fears of higher U.S. interest rates in the
wake of strong economic data and a weak bond market.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) shed 8.02 points to end
at 2,097.40 points in thin trading, again falling through the
2,100-mark.
</P>
<P>
The total volume dropped to 131.74 million shares valued at
407.10 million Singapore dollars (about 240.50 million U.S.
dollars). Decliners outstripped advancers by 204 to 69 with 173
counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Gen Int remained at top on the volume list with a turnover of
16.69 million shares. It was followed by SingTel which registered
a volume of 9.24 million units. AFP was the next with 7.31 million
counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 led the gainers of the day as it picked up 50 cents
to close at 17.90 Singapore dollars. SPH and UOB moved up 30 cents
to finish at 27.30 and 12.90 Singapore dollars respectively. DBS
and SIA DBScw00 edged down 20 cents to end at 20.20 and 9.80
Singapore dollars separately.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Venture led the descent of the day as it sank
60 cents to close at 15.20 Singapore dollars. PacCent trimmed 45
cents to finish at 9.05 Singapore dollars. Asean and GE Life
retreated 40 cents and ended at 8.50 U.S. dollars and 18.30
Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said shares prices closed weaker as sentiment was
affected by the overnight fall on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
They also said worries over the escalating violence in East
Timor also weighed much on the market sentiment.
</P>
<P>
They noted that dealers were cautious ahead of the release of
key economic data by Japan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
