<HEADLINE> Gold Price In Hong Kong Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The gold price in Hong Kong
rose eight HK dollars to close at 2,368 HK dollars a tael on
Wednesday, according to Po Sang Bank, one of the major gold
dealers in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The gold price is equivalent to 255.97 U.S. dollars a troy
ounce, up 0.87 U.S. dollars at Wednesday's exchange rate of one U.
S. dollar against 7.7655 HK dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
