<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks fell 39.46
points, or 0.29 percent, to close at 13,356.63 Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Market turnover was 5.733 billion HK dollars (735 million U.S.
dollars), 2.725 billion HK dollars (349 million U.S. dollars) less
than Tuesday's turnover of 8.458 billion HK dollars (1.084 billion
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Sectoral sub-indexes for finance, utilities, properties and
commerce and industry made across-the-board decreases of 0.02
percent, 0.35 percent, 0.41 percent and 0.58 percent,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
China-related shares ended with the Hang Seng China Enterprises
Index down 1.01 percent while the Hang Seng China-Affiliated
Corporations Index down 0.80 percent.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index gained 5.37 points, or 0.04 percent, to
open at 13,401.46 on Wednesday. The stocks fell 15.03 points, or 0.
11 percent, to finish Wednesday's morning session at 13,381.06.
</P>
</TEXT>
