<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Reduce, Remit Taxation on Overseas-Funded Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- China will take a series of
measures to reduce or remit taxation on foreign funded enterprises,
a Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC)
official announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Taxation on equipment, technology, fittings and spare parts
introduced by high-tech and export oriented enterprises and
research and development centers involving foreign funds for the
purpose of technological upgrading will be exempted from import
tariffs in line with certain regulations, according to Ma Xiuhong,
MOFTEC assistant minister, at the China Fair for Investment and
Trade.
</P>
<P>
The business tax will be remitted when foreign-funded
enterprises transfer their technology to Chinese enterprises, Ma
said.
</P>
<P>
"The income tax will be even exempted for foreign-funded
enterprises involving advanced technology or with favorable
conditions after approval from the State taxation departments,"
she added.
</P>
<P>
And the sales tax from technological transfer by foreign-funded
enterprises and research and development centers will also be
exempted.
</P>
<P>
"Some foreign funded enterprises will enjoy preferential
taxation treatment when purchasing domestic equipment," Ma said.
</P>
<P>
China will also improve the services for foreign funded
enterprises in terms of finance, management and legal system and
encourage foreign business people to invest in economically less
advantaged central and western parts, she said, adding that
foreign funds will be permitted to flow into more projects.
</P>
</TEXT>
