<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OECD to Help China Attract More Foreign Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Organization for Economic
Cooperation and Development (OECD) will help China attract more
foreign capital, its secretary-general said today.
</P>
<P>
Donald Johnston described China as the group's most important
cooperative partner, and that since they began working together in
1995, the areas of their cooperation have rapidly expanded.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have collaborated to study enterprise reform,
train workers in the Chinese tax departments, and analyze
statistics. Others areas of cooperation include agriculture,
education, environment and investment.
</P>
<P>
He said that his organization predicts China will be the world'
s largest economic body by 2020, adding that China is appealing to
foreign investors, and a great deal of long-term capital has
flooded into the country.
</P>
<P>
This is because that China has abundant natural resources,
enormous labor supply and has implemented a series of policies
aiming at luring foreign investment, he said.
</P>
<P>
Johnston said that he will travel to Beijing to discuss ways to
promote cooperation with China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
