<HEADLINE> Chinese, Guinean Military Leaders Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian met today with Ibrahima Diallo, chief of general staff of
the Guinean army.
</P>
<P>
Chi said that although the two countries are far away, the
friendship between the two peoples goes back to ancient times.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also vice chairman of the Central Military Commission and
state councilor, said that as two developing countries, China and
Guinea have common interests in many aspects and have reached
consensus on important international matters.
</P>
<P>
He said he believes Diallo's China visit will be successful.
</P>
<P>
Diallo said that the Guinean people always receive support from
the Chinese people. He expressed the hope that the visit will add
to the bilateral friendship.
</P>
<P>
Diallo started his nine-day visit on September 6, at the
invitation of his Chinese counterpart Fu Quanyou. 
</P>
