<DOCNO> XIE19990908.0151 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Seek More Overseas Investment in Central-Western Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ma announced the move at the ongoing China Fair for Investment
and Trade hosted in Xiamen, a coastal city in east China's Fujian
Province.
</P>
<P>
"China will loosen conditions for setting up overseas-funded
enterprises and overseas investors' shareholding proportion in
enterprises in the central and western areas, which are
economically-underdeveloped as compared with coastal areas in the
eastern and southern areas," she said.
</P>
<P>
According to Ma, overseas-funded enterprises in the areas will
enjoy a 15-percent tax incentive for three more years after the
current term matures. At the same time, enterprises with over 25
percent overseas investment will enjoy the same preferential
policies as overseas-funded firms.
</P>
<P>
"In addition, overseas-funded enterprises already in operation
in coastal areas are encouraged to make investment or operate
business in overseas-funded or domestic enterprises in the central
and western areas," she said.
</P>
<P>
With the approval of the State Council, the enterprises will be
free from tariffs while importing equipment, technological
facilities, fittings, and spare parts.
</P>
<P>
And China will allow development zones in the provinces and
autonomous regions of the central and western areas to apply for
the status as state-level economic and technological development
zones. But the number will be restricted to one for every province
or provincial capital.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 80 percent of overseas investment for the
country are made in coastal areas. "There is a great need for
expansion of overseas investment in China's central and western
areas," Ma stressed.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Government has given top priority to sprucing up
the country's central and western areas. Policies and measures,
including tax incentives, increase of fixed-asset investment, and
preferential terms for overseas investors, have been adopted to
accelerate the development pace of the region.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
