<HEADLINE> India's Cement Output Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- India's Cumulative cement
output reached 38.71 million tons in the first five months of the
1999-2000 fiscal year (April-August), up 21.35 percent over 31.90
million tons recorded in the same period of the previous fiscal
year.
</P>
<P>
According to the provisional figures released by the Cement
Manufacturers' Association, the cement output in August stood at
6.90 million tons, an increase of 17.55 percent over 5.87 million
tons recorded in the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
Industry observers said that the trend in cement production has
been on expected lines with the growth rate for the entire year
likely to taper towards 12-13 percent. 
