<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New China Grows Amid Stability (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three years later, the macro-economic control measures adopted
by the central government reached the anticipated targets, the
national economy successfully realized a "soft landing", providing
a solid basis for national economy to enjoy a fast, sustainable
and healthy development in a fairly long period, as well as for
the country to enjoy a long-term political and social stability.
</P>
<P>
The "soft landing" not only helped China to minimize the risks
arising from the subsequent Asian financial crisis, but also
enabled China to maintain its currency stable, contributing
greatly to protecting regional economic stability, which has been
generally acknowledged by the international community.
</P>
<P>
Concentrating on its modernization drive, China needs a stable
environment both domestically and internationally, especially
friendly relations with neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 50 years, China has always devoted to global
peace and stability. So far China has signed boundary agreements
with 10 of its 15 neighbors, creating the best time of
relationship with neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese people have suffered bitterly from alien invasions
and wars in history, this is the first time in China's modern
history since the Opium War that the nation is able to concentrate
on construction amid peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
More and more people from the international community have held
that China's stability and development have strong impact on both
Asian and global peace and development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
