<HEADLINE> Torrential Rains Kill 153 People in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Torrential rains that hit the
southern part of Zhejiang, a coastal province in east China, last
Saturday have resulted in the deaths of 153 people, according to
local officials.
</P>
<P>
The heavy rain, causing mountain flooding and landslides, swept
across the cities of Wenzhou and Taizhou and Lishui Prefecture.
</P>
<P>
Rain inundated seven counties, and affected seven others and
233 townships. Floodwaters also affected 4.92 million people,
besieged 1,028 villages and left 10,600 people homeless in the
three areas.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, 117,000 hectares of crops were damaged and some major
hydro-electric, transportation and communication facilities were
destroyed.
</P>
<P>
The State and provincial governments have sent rescue teams to
the flooded areas. Some 720,000 people have been evacuated to
safer areas, the officials added.
</P>
<P>
This past June, a severe flood hit northern part of Zhejiang,
killing 32 people and causing economic loss of about 10.5 billion
yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
