<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin: China's Stance on Taiwan Issue Remains Firm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- China stands "very firm" on
the principle of safeguarding sovereignty and territorial
integrity, visiting Chinese President Jiang Zemin said here
Wednesday during talks with Australian Prime Minister John Howard.
</P>
<P>
He said that Lee Teng-hui's recent "two states" remarks
represent a very dangerous step towards splitting China, as their
essence is to completely defy and abandon the internationally
acclaimed "one China" stance.
</P>
<P>
Lee's separatist remarks and activities have damaged the
stability in Taiwan and undermined the political basis of the
cross-straits relations, leading to tension and deterioration in
the cross-straits relations, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed China's strong opposition to any remarks or
activity aimed at undermining China's sovereignty and territorial
integrity, saying that the country is against the "two Chinas" and
the "one China, one Taiwan" viewpoints, or any attempt or activity
that leads to Taiwan's independence.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed appreciation of Australian leaders' remarks in
favor of the "one China" policy on many occasions.
</P>
<P>
Howard, on his part, reiterated Australia's stand of firmly
following the "one China" policy.  
</P>
