<HEADLINE> Manila to Create Drug Enforcement Administration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine Congress has
approved in principle the creation of a Drug Enforcement
Administration (DEA), a super body to spearhead the drive against
drugs in the country.
</P>
<P>
This was released Wednesday by Representative Roilo Golez in
his speech at the celebration of the 33rd founding anniversary of
the National Police Commission (Napolcom).
</P>
<P>
He said if the DEA will be formed, the Philippine National
Police (PNP) will be freed from the task of combating drugs and it
could concentrate on the keeping of peace and order. 
</P>
