<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uganda's Coffee Export Rises Steady </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's coffee exports during
the past coffee year from October 1998 to August 1999 show steady
rise in both volume and value.
</P>
<P>
The export volume and value has risen by 21.4 percent and 3.5
percent respectively compared to the same period last year,
according to a monthly report of the Uganda Coffee Development
Authority.
</P>
<P>
Coffee exports made so far this year stand at 3.43 million bags
(60 kilograms per bag), an increase of 13.1 percent over the
1997/98 cumulative total, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The report attributed the improvement in the level of
performance volume- wise to the generally good weather and better
husbandry practices due to enhance extension services.
</P>
<P>
Cumulative value of exports for the same period stood at 268
million U.S. dollars, up from 260 million dollars in the
corresponding period of last season.
</P>
<P>
Plummeting prices on the international market is blamed for the
 relatively low percentage rise in value.
</P>
<P>
Coffee is Uganda's top foreign exchange earner followed by fish
and cotton. Coffee export accounts for more than half of the
country's foreign exchange reserves. 
</P>
</TEXT>
