<HEADLINE> Zambia's Exports to Botswana to Reach $20M </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Zambia's exports to Botswana
are expected to exceed 20 million U.S. dollars this year, the
Times of Zambia newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Botswana would be able to meet all the orders of Botswana,
which mainly on building materials which were in high demand of
the booming construction industry.
</P>
<P>
Export Board of Zambia Executive Director, Johnson Mwenya, said
in a statement released Tuesday that there had been a tremendous
increase in inquiries from Botswana which had more than doubled.
</P>
<P>
Mwenya who led a contingent of 14 local companies to the just
ended Botswana International Trade Fair in Gaborone, said Zambia
Sugar and Chilanga Cement PLC were among the exhibitors which
received inquires worth about 4.5 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The inquires were mainly for molasses, cement and food stuffs
such as beans, ground-nuts and dried fish.
</P>
<P>
Mwenya said the five-day event saw Zambia emerge winners,
pushing Britain into second position while Swaziland for the
third.
</P>
<P>
Other countries present were Lesotho, Mali, Pakistan, Iran,
Ghana and Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
Zambia exhibited high quality goods like hardwood doors and
parquet flooring, particle boards, handicrafts, garments and
textiles, he said. 
</P>
