<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan is mulling over its
final decision on the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty (CTBT) because
the U.S. Congressional action on the removal of sanctions against
Islamabad is still pending.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani Foreign Minister Sartaj Aziz told reporters Wednesday
that Pakistan is "making an assessment of what the U.S. Congress
is going to decide."
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Congress is right now seized of the matter of U.S.
sanctions imposed on both Pakistan and India in the wake of their
respective nuclear tests in May last year.
</P>
<P>
When asked if Pakistan has decided not to ink the CTBT, Aziz
said, "it is still under consideration because Congressional
action is pending."
</P>
<P>
Unless the U.S. Congressional action is known, there cannot be
a decision by Pakistan in this regard, said Aziz. 
