<DOCNO> XIE19990908.0201 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New China Grows Amid Stability (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Over the past month, China has
concentrated its efforts on exposing and criticizing the fallacies
of the Falun Gong cult, and the great power and effectiveness of
the struggle demonstrates the close attention the Chinese
government stresses on political stability and its determination
to protect that status.
</P>
<P>
When meeting with the former President of the United States
George Bush in early 1989, Deng Xiaoping, architect of China's
opening up and reform policies, said that "for China, the
overwhelming need is stability." This has been reiterated and
confirmed by President Jiang Zemin in recent times.
</P>
<P>
Fifty years of New China's development has proven that their
assessment of the situation is correct, and this has increasingly
been acknowledged by overseas people.
</P>
<P>
Reviewing New China's half century of history, there were
periods of stable development. Shortly after the founding of the
People's Republic, the central government adopted the principle of
concentrating on the development of social productive forces in an
bid to gradually meet people's growing material and cultural needs.
</P>
<P>
During the first Five-Year Plan period (1953-1957), the output
value of industry and agriculture grew 18 percent and 4.5 percent,
respectively, while a number of key infrastructure projects that
were critical to the national economy and people's livelihoods
were completed.
</P>
<P>
However, there were also bitter lessons to be learned when
instability seriously harmed the national economy and social
development. This social unrest resulted from the "Cultural
Revolution" (1966-1976), known as the "Ten-year catastrophe",
which drove the national economy to the verge of destruction.
</P>
<P>
The "Cultural Revolution" left all businesses in China awaiting
rejuvenation. The second generation leaders of the Communist Party
led by Deng Xiaoping correctly judged the situation and timely
shifted the Party and the government's working focus from
political struggle to economic construction.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990908.0202 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
