<HEADLINE> China to Attend CeBIT 2000 Hannover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A total of 16 IT companies
from the mainland, 78 from Hong Kong and 502 from Taiwan will
participate in the CeBIT 2000, the world's biggest IT trade fair
held in Hannover, Germany.
</P>
<P>
"So many Chinese exhibitors have demonstrated that they are
very successful in the IT fields and have played an important role
in the world IT industry," said Eberhard Roloff, director of press
and public relations of Hannover Exhibition Company, the organizer
of the fair.
</P>
<P>
Over 7,500 exhibitors are expected to show their products and
technologies in 26 halls covering an area of more than 400,000
square meters during the show from February 24 to March 1 next
year.
</P>
<P>
Near 850 exhibitors will come from the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
"The large number of exhibitors from this region assumes even
greater significance in view of the economic status of Asia on the
world stage," Roloff said here today.
</P>
<P>
According to him, the display categories for CeBIT 2000 include
information technology, network computing, automatic data capture,
software consulting and services, telecommunications, office
automation, bank technology, card technology and security
equipment and research and technology transfer.
</P>
<P>
"An extensive program of joint displays, conferences, forum
events and company presentations completes the list of attractions,
" he added.
</P>
<P>
"Launched in 1986, the CeBIT has witnessed a constant increase
of exhibitors and visitors. It is expected to attract about 600,
000 to 70,000 visitors this time," Roloff noted.  
</P>
