<HEADLINE> Shanghai Reports Stable Rise In Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai exported 1.667
billion US dollars of goods in August, bringing the total for the
first eight months of this year to nearly 11.447 billion US
dollars, an 18 percent rise on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
The city has been further improving its export mix, increasing
the exports of hi-tech and hi-value-added products and the
processing trade with imported raw materials.
</P>
<P>
Exports by local overseas funded businesses are rising
dramatically, and local state-run enterprises have halted their
declining export record.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has set a goal to handle 16.5 billion US dollars of
exports for the whole of the year. 
</P>
