<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Official on Adjustments of Dong, Dollar Exchange Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- There would be no sudden
adjustment of the exchange rate between the Vietnamese dong (VND)
and the U.S. dollar like last year, Vietnam's business newspaper
The Saigon Times Daily Wednesday quoted an official of the State
Bank of Vietnam as saying.
</P>
<P>
However, as the dollar is strengthening against VND on
Vietnam's Interbank market, the Vietnam's central bank will
continue to make gradual adjustments in this direction in the
upcoming months.
</P>
<P>
A Vietnam's bank official admitted that over the past three
months, the U.S. dollar appreciated against VND by 30 VND per
dollar each month.
</P>
<P>
The exchange rate announced on Tuesday by Vietnam's central
bank was 13,964 VND to a U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnam's bank official said that the exchange rate will be
adjusted in line with market movements and how wide the adjustment
should be depends on the balance of foreign currency supply and
demand in each quarter.
</P>
<P>
"In previous years demand for the greenback often increased
from September due to businesses boosting imports to prepare for
the Lunar New Year Festival, but this year the demand has softened
due to shrinking trade deficit," the Vietnamese official said.
</P>
</TEXT>
