<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-08 07:56 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkish Building Contractor to Be Sentenced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Building contractor Veli
Gocer, who built numerous shoddy apartments in western Turkey, 90
percent of which collapsed in last month's earthquake, is expected
to be given prison terms of between four and 10 years.
</P>
<P>
Local Daily News reported Wednesday that Gocer was arrested on
Monday in a friend's house in Alibeykoy in Istanbul, the largest
city of Turkey, and was then sent to the Bursa E-Type Prison in
western Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The crushed buildings set up by Gocer caused the deaths of
thousands of people and the public prosecutor's office in Yalova
province issued an arrest warrant in absentia for him last week,
the English-language newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Gocer confessed to having used poor quality concrete in his
buildings, a practice that would cut costs but threatens the
structural integrity of the buildings.
</P>
<P>
Gocer, who fled out of fear of being lynched after the monster
quake, said earlier he used substandard materials in construction,
and that the houses were in poor conditions.
</P>
<P>
Shoddy construction was widely blamed for the high death toll
in the 7.4-magnitude earthquake hitting northwestern Turkey on
August 17. Some 14,000 people were confirmed dead so far but
government officials feared that as many as 40,000 people could
have been killed in the quake as many are still listed as
missing. 
</P>
