<HEADLINE> Vietnam Boosts Footwear Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam has exported 920 million
U.S. dollars worth of footwear in the first eight months of this
year, up 25 percent over the same period last year, press reports
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
With the current export tempo, the country can obtain a
turnover of 1.4 billion U.S. dollars from footwear exports this
year, 200 million dollars higher than previously planned, the
reports said quoting an official of the Vietnam Footwear
Corporation.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the European Union and regional countries, which
are the traditional markets of the Vietnamese footwear, this
year's footwear exports to the United States could nearly double
last year's figure of around 100 million dollars, said the
official.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnam Footwear Corporation plans to spend 120 billion
Vietnamese dong (about 8.6 million dollars) to expand production
in some shoe companies.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese footwear corporation has also worked out a
development plan to 2010 to triple its current annual output of
some 900 million pairs of shoes and sandals, the official said.
</P>
</TEXT>
