<HEADLINE> Ancient Antiques Exhibition Held in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- An ancient jewelry and artistic
antiques exhibition is on show here, sponsored by the Department
of Archaeology of the Myanmar Ministry of Culture.
</P>
<P>
The six-day exhibition, which was opened Tuesday, is aimed at
preventing antiques from being smuggled out of the country by
inspiring Myanmar people to make a habit of cherishing and
preserving antiques and uplifting dynamism of patriotic spirit
through cherishing and preserving Myanmar cultural antiques.
</P>
<P>
Over 300 antiques from the country's five different ancient
periods -- Pyu, Bagan, Innwa, Konbaung and Yadanabon -- are on
display at the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
In September last year, Myanmar enacted the Protection and
Preservation of Cultural Heritage Regions Law in an effort to
prevent smuggling antiques to foreign countries and to recover
those that have been taken outside the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
