<HEADLINE> Chinese Investment, Trade Fair Opens In East China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Third Chinese investment
and trade fair opened in the eastern port city of Xiamen today
when State Councilor Wu Yi unlocked the gate of the Fushan
International Exhibition Town, the fair's venue, with a gold-
plated key.
</P>
<P>
The fair, which opens today and will last through September 12,
at the sponsorship of the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation. More than 6,000 business people from overseas and 44
delegations from Chinese provinces, government departments, and
organizations are attending. Multinationals like Motorola, Nokia,
Exxon, and GE have several of the more than 100 booths.
</P>
<P>
The fair has a special hall for the 25 groups of Taiwanese
business people attending. There are 13,000 projects available for
investment and 1,000 projects that need about 10 billion U.S.
dollars worth of investment are expected to result in contracts.
</P>
<P>
There will be a symposium on international investment and
cooperation for the 21st century, seminars on mobile phone
telecommunications and the building materials industry, and a
round-table of the Organization for Economic Cooperation and
Development during the fair.
</P>
<P>
Fuzhou, the capital of Fujian Province, has already signed
contracts with overseas investors on 41 projects worth 511 million
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
By late July, China had reported 334,000 overseas invested
businesses, with contracts worth 594.81 billion U.S. dollars, 288.
94 billion dollars of which had been paid in. 
</P>
