<HEADLINE> Austrian Unemployment Rate Falls to 5.3 Percent in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Austrian unemployment rate
in August fell to 5.3 percent from 5.9 percent in the
corresponding month of last year, said the Austrian labor market
service bureau on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Compared with last year, employment has increased by 48,000 to
3,209,000 so far this year, according to the figures published by
the bureau.
</P>
<P>
The jobless figure decreased by 1,089 from that of July to 180,
243 in August, down 0.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference on Tuesday, Austrian Minister of Health,
Labor and Social Affairs Lore Hostasch said that the unemployed in
all provinces, all sectors and all age groups has declined. The
number of unemployed people under 25 has decreased the most.
</P>
<P>
Also, 26,490 people were receiving training for re-employment
in August and they were excluded in calculating the unemployment
rate. 
</P>
