<HEADLINE> Chinese Company to Build Paper Mill for Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese Tianjin company has
reached a 3-million-U.S.-dollar contract with Myanmar to build a
25-ton newsprint paper mill in the country's central Mandalay
division.
</P>
<P>
Under the contract signed here Tuesday between the Tianjin
Machinery Import and Export Corporation of China and the Paper and
Chemical Industries of the Myanmar Ministry of Industry No.1, the
recycle newsprint paper mill is to be built in Paleik in the
division, official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the contract, the Chinese side will carry out the
design of the plant and provide related machinery and equipment,
as well as extend technical supervision and train Myanmar
technicians.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar side will undertake the construction of the mill.
</P>
<P>
The paper mill, which will produce import-substitute paper,
will be completed in one and a half years.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, Myanmar produced 16,803 tons
of all sorts of paper and imported 49.76 million U.S. dollars'
worth of paper, paper board and products in fiscal 1998-99 which
ended in March. 
</P>
