<HEADLINE> Milosevic Calls for Respect for Yugoslav Sovereignty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic said Tuesday here that the UN special representative for
Kosovo must respect the state sovereignty and territorial
integrity of Yugoslavia and protect residents of all ethnic in
Kosovo when carrying out his duty.
</P>
<P>
He said this when meeting Russian First Deputy Foreign Minister
Alexander Avdeyev, who arrived here Sunday for an official visit.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav president and Russian minister noted that ethnic
Albanian terrorists are still rampant in Kosovo and the
international peace keeping force constantly violates the relevant
UN resolutions, thus seriously threatening the regional stability
and political solution of the crisis.
</P>
<P>
Milosevic also demanded a quick end to terrorism and anarchism,
disarmament of the "Kosovo Liberation Army" and permission for the
Yugoslav police to enter Kosovo so as to create conditions for
refugees home coming.
</P>
<P>
On his part, Avdeyev expressed support to Yugoslavia's
principled stand on the Kosovo issue, saying the Russian troops in
the peace keeping force will perform their mission according to
the UN resolutions.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, when meeting Yugoslav Foreign Minister Zivadin
Jovanovic, Avdeyev pointed out that certain peace-keeping
operations in Kosovo by western nations in fact worked to split
Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Bernard Kouchner, UN special representative for Kosovo, was
accused of trampling upon the sovereignty of Yugoslavia and going
against the UN resolution for his September 4 decision that German
mark would serve as the major official currency in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
In August, the UN Interim Administration Mission in Kosovo, led
by Kouchner, set about to establish a separate customs service for
Kosovo, which was termed by Yugoslavia as "a flagrant violation"
of June 10 Security Council resolution, particularly its
provisions regarding Yugoslavia's sovereignty and territorial
integrity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
