<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Economic Zone Built in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Work on a new economic zone
commenced recently near the newly-built Wuhu Yangtze River Bridge.
</P>
<P>
The economic zone is aimed at making the best of the bridge,
which is one of the key infrastructure projects in China.
</P>
<P>
The economic zone covers an area of 9.15 square kilometers
between the Wuhu Economic and Technological Development Zone and
the existing city proper of Wuhu, in east China's Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
Its construction will be divided into two phases. During the
first phase, scenic spots will be built along the river and a
trunk road will be paved. Tourist, business, high-tech and
residential zones will be built. In the 2001-2005 period, efforts
will be made to turn the economic zone into modernized new city.
</P>
<P>
The Yangtze River Bridge at Wuhu is the last highway-railway
bridge China builds in this century. It is expected to be
completed by the end of 2000.  
</P>
