<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2,000-Year Old Tombs Discovered In Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese archaeologists have
found a group of 40 tombs that date back to between the Western
Han Dynasty (206-24 B.C.) and the Tang Dynasty (618-907) in the
city of Yuzhou in Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 bronze, jade, and iron items and pieces of
pottery have been unearthed from the tombs. Among these relics was
a rare dragon-shaped pottery figurine.
</P>
<P>
The discovery is expected to provide valuable clues to the
study of funeral customs in the region, the archaeologists say.
</P>
</TEXT>
