<HEADLINE> Men's 2,000 Meters World Record Evolution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Following is the evolution of
the men's 2,000 meters world record since the introduction of
electronic timing (tabulated under time, name, nationality, venue,
date):
</P>
<P>
4:51.39  Steve Cram, Britain, Budapest, August 4, 1985
</P>
<P>
4:50.81  Said Aouita, Morocco, Paris, July 16, 1987
</P>
<P>
4:47.88  Noureddine Morceli, Algeria, Paris, July 3, 1995
</P>
<P>
4:44.79  Hicham El Guerrouj, Morocco, Berlin, September 7,
1999
</P>
