<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Beats Argentina 4-2 in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRAZILIA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Rivaldo scored a hattrick as
Brazil beat Argentina 4-2 on Tuesday in an exhibition game in
Porto Alegre, Brazil, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Brazil, coming off a 2-0 loss to Argentina on Sunday in Buenos
Aires, pressured Argentina from the opening minutes.
</P>
<P>
After two goals from Rivaldo were ruled offside, the Brazilian
star got it right, drawing out goalkeeper Bonano and firing it
past him. Rivaldo scored again two minutes later, with a header
off a feed from Roberto Carlos.
</P>
<P>
Argentina made it 2-1 in the 45th minute when Ayala scored on a
header off a feed from Veron.
</P>
<P>
Rivaldo scored his third goal in the 70th minute off a feed by
Ronaldo. Then it was Ronaldo's turn in the 82nd minute with a left-
foot shot from the center.
</P>
<P>
Ortega scored the game's last goal for Argentina in 88th minute
dribbling past a handful of Brazilian defenders. 
</P>
</TEXT>
