<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Japanese Friendship Forest Built in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-Japanese friendship
forest is being built in the city of Shizuishan in northwest China
's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region to mark the fifth anniversary of
the establishment of friendly relationships between Shizuishan and
the Japanese city of Hamada.
</P>
<P>
So far, over 2,000 different kinds of trees from both China and
Japan have been planted in the eight hectare forest inside a big
park on the Gobi desert outside the city. With 300 hectares of
land, the huge park on the Gobi desert used to be a vast area of
desert. But now over 300,000 trees have been planted in the area,
turning more than 200,000 square kilometers of its land into green
fields.
</P>
<P>
"The planting of the forest will be completed at the end of 2,
000," according to the city's mayor Ma Ruiwen.
</P>
<P>
Shizuishan is the second biggest city in Ningxia while Hamada
is a port city in southwestern Japan. The two cities established
friendly twinning arrangements in November 1994 to seek better
cooperation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990908.0276 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Landscape Festival for South China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, September 8 (Xinhua)-- Guilin, a popular tourist
destination in south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region,
will hold its seventh landscape festival from November 22 to
December 31.
</P>
<P>
Guilin has a typical karst land formation, and is noted for its
green mountains, clear water, fascinating caverns and grotesque
shaped stones. Its mountains and waters are considered by many to
be the finest under heaven.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, this year's landscape festival will
feature a range of cultural activities and special tours to
highlight this famous Chinese scenic city's long history, great
culture and the current changes it is undergoing.
</P>
<P>
As the festival coincides with the 2110th anniversary of the
founding of the city, officials also plan to invite delegations
from foreign cities that have built friendly ties with Guilin,
overseas magicians, and tourist organizations from Hong Kong,
Macao and Taiwan to attend the festival and promote friendship.
</P>
<P>
Planned activities for the event include a gala song and dance
shows, the Guilin International Magic Invitation Tournament, a
photographic display marking the city's founding anniversary,
cockfighting, a parade to celebrate the return of Macao to the
motherland on December 20 and a Christmas party on December 25.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990908.0277 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade Fair for Shijiazhuang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Delegations from 25
countries and regions have, so far, promised to attend a foreign
trade fair scheduled for the capital city of north China's Hebei
Province between October 9-12.
</P>
<P>
The '99 Shijiazhuang Foreign Trade Fair is sponsored by the
China Chamber of International Commerce (CCIC) and the China
Council for the Promotion of International Trade (CCPIT).
</P>
<P>
The participants will mainly come from North America, Europe,
Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan, said Chen Chunfeng, chairman of the
CCIC.
</P>
<P>
"The fair will cover sectors such as agriculture, horticulture,
water control, environmental protection, machinery, building
materials, medicine and food," Chen said.
</P>
<P>
Hebei province will take the opportunity to attract foreign
funds to develop its agriculture, basic facilities and technology
upgrading.  
</P>
</TEXT>
