<HEADLINE> Myanmar-Malaysia Bilateral Trade Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Bilateral trade between Myanmar
and Malaysia amounted to 257.19 million U.S. dollars in fiscal
1998-99 which ended in March, up 32.89 percent compared with that
of the previous fiscal year which was 193.53 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The official Economic Indicators say in its latest issue that
of the total bilateral trade in 1998-99, Myanmar's imports from
Malaysia were valued at 200 million dollars, 20.48 percent more
than the figure in the previous fiscal year which was 166 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar's exports to Malaysia in the fiscal year stood at 57.19
million dollars, increasing by 107.73 percent over the previous
fiscal year which was 27.53 million dollars, it adds.
</P>
<P>
In addition to trade link, the economic cooperation between
Myanmar and Malaysia was also strengthened. During the five-year
period from April 1994 to April 1999, Myanmar absorbed investments
amounting to 533 million dollars from Malaysia in 22 projects.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia is third after Singapore and Thailand in the line-up
of investments from member countries of the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
