<HEADLINE> Myanmar-Indonesia Bilateral Trade Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Bilateral trade between Myanmar
and Indonesia reached 233.7 million U.S. dollars in fiscal 1998-99
which ended in March, up 76.37 percent compared with that of the
previous year which was 132.5 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest figures released by Myanmar's Central
Statistical Organization, Myanmar's imports from Indonesia
amounted to 210 million dollars in 1998-99, up 86 percent over the
previous fiscal year which was 112.9 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
In 1998-99, Myanmar's exports to Indonesia came to 23.7 million
dollars, up 20.92 percent compared with the previous fiscal year
which was 19.6 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
After joining the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN), Myanmar's bilateral trade with member countries of the
regional grouping including Indonesia increased sharply.
</P>
<P>
According to other official statistics, during the five-year
period from April 1994 to April 1999, Myanmar absorbed 237.42
million dollars' investment from Indonesia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
