<P>
BUENAS AIRES, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Paraguay's new Foreign
Minister Jose Felix Fernandez said on Tuesday that the conflict
with Argentina and Uruguay will be resolved in the near future.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here from Ascuncion, Paraguay,
the Paraguayan foreign minister said he is "convinced that our
differences over the concept of political asylum" may be solved in
the short term "because relations have not been broken off."
</P>
<P>
The discrepancies between Paraguay, Argentina and Uruguay
developed last Friday, due to the negative responses from the
governments of Argentina and Uruguay to concede the extradition of
Paraguay's ex general Lino Oviedo and ex Defense Minister Jose
Segovia Boltes.
</P>
<P>
For their parts, Argentine President Carlos Menem and Uruguay
President Julio Maria Sanguinetti decided to consult their
embassadors to Paraguay.
</P>
<P>
The government of Uruguay on Monday called back its ambassador
to Paraguay following the Paraguayan government's recall of its
ambassadors to Uruguay and Argentina last Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
