<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock Exchange
on Tuesday closed with the benchmark IPC index falling by 140.97
points, or 2.79 percent, to 4,910.06 points.
</P>
<P>
Operators exchanged 46.285 million shares worth some 85.756
million U.S. dollars against 6.809 million shares for an amount of
some 10.5 milion dollars on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The local currency, peso, mantained stable at 9.45 to one
dollar for sale and 9.15 for purchase in the main exchange houses
of the Mexico City. 
</P>
</TEXT>
