<HEADLINE> Japan Beats Ghana in Bangladeshi Soccer International Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cup was handed to the winners by Bangladeshi Prime Minister
Sheikh Hasina, who watched the final of the Second Bangabandhu Cup
International Football Tournament, which started on August 27, at
the Bangabandhu Stadium.
</P>
<P>
The champion team would get 6,000 U.S. dollars as prize money,
and the runners-up would get 4,000 dollars. The player of the 12-
day tournament and the highest scorer would also receive 2,000
dollars each.
</P>
<P>
Japan and Ghana entered the final after beating South Korea and
Hungary respectively last Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Twelve teams from Hungary, Malaysia, Bangladesh, Brasazil,
South Korea, Thailand, Ghana, Uzbekistan, Nepal, Japan, Kuwait and
Indonesia were participated in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
The inaugural Bangabandhu Gold Cup was held here from December
1996 to January 1997, which attracted 10 foreign teams and three
local sides. 
</P>
</TEXT>
