<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Athletes Fly to Johannesburg for All Africa Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- An Ethiopian sports
delegation, spcializing in athletics, boxing, cycling,
weightlifting and table tennis, left here Tuesday for Johannesburg,
South Africa, to participate in the 7th All Africa Games.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian world track star Haile Gebreselassie remains at
home due to injuries on his left toe and blisters on his right
heel, sports officials said.
</P>
<P>
However, other track stars like Gete Wami, the women's 10,000m
gold medalist at the August Seville world championships, 5,000m
bronze medalist Ayelech Worku, 1,500m bronze medalist Kutre
Dulecha who won the gold medal in the 6th All Africa Games, and 10,
000m men's bronze medalist Assefa Mezgebu are expected to bring
medals for the country.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that disabled athletes will for the first time
compete in the coming continental games. Ethiopia said it would
have two representatives in the competition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
