<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Philippine newspapers Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Manila Bulletin:
</P>
<P>
-- Philippine President Joseph Estrada will sign into law
Wednesday a measure resetting the regular elections for officials
of the Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao from September 13,
1999 to the second Monday of September 2000.
</P>
<P>
Philippine Daily Inquirer:
</P>
<P>
-- Manila Archbishop Jaime Cardinal Sin will lead a rally on
September 21 to let government leaders know that the people will
not "play blind to the immorality we see in the government."
</P>
<P>
Business World:
</P>
<P>
-- The Philippine government proposed Tuesday a financial
sector tax reform package that aims to remove the gross receipts
tax on banks and reduce the documentary stamp tax, among other
things. 
