<HEADLINE> Over 2,000 Earthquakes Shakes Arequipa, Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The province of Arequipa in south
Peru has so far this year been shaken by 2,193 tremors of
different intensity, said an expert on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Director of the Geophysical Institute of Arequipa Hector Palza
Arias said that 1,829 were telluric movements in the local area.
</P>
<P>
In August alone, seven tremors were detected, of which six were
registered grade 2 on the Mercalli scale and one of grade 3.
</P>
<P>
The latest, which was on April 3 this year, with an intensity
of 6.5 on the modified scale of Mercalli. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990908.0305 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chile's Overseas Investment Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Chile's investment abroad in
the first eight months was only 807 million U.S. dollars, falling
53 percent compared with the same period of last year, Santiago
Chamber of Commerce said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Chile invested in foreign countries mainly in the section of
industry, with 52.7 percent of the total, followed by energy with
29.4 percent and services with 11.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Receiving 36.5 percent of the capital, Peru has become the
major destination of the Chilean investment, followed by the
Dominican Republic with 22 percent and Argentina with 18.6 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990908.0306 </DOCNO>
