<HEADLINE> Chile's Foreign Debt Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Chile's foreign debt reached
34.21 billion U.S. dollars as of July 31, with an increase of 2.52
billion dollars in the first seven months of 1999, the Central
Bank announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Among the total debt, 28.27 billion dollars are private debt
and the other part belongs to public sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
