<DOCNO> XIE19990908.0309 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greece Announces Plan for Balkan Reconstruction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Greek Economy Minister Yiannos
Papantoniou said Tuesday that his country could spend 100 billion
drachmas (about 331 million U.S. dollars) in a five-year plan
aimed to help in an economic reconstruction of the Balkans.
</P>
<P>
Papantoniou said that the money would be raised from the state
budget and from private sources.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that he would meet his Balkan counterparts in
the northern Greek city of Thessaloniki next month to discuss the
Greek plan, which could support actions in the sectors of
infrastructure, services and trade.
</P>
<P>
The plan envisages that financial aid would be based on
conditions prevailing in each country, damage assessment, economic
and social growth and their ability to absorb funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
